quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  16,85,"And when those who wronged see the punishment, it will not be lightened for them, nor will they be reprieved."
  16,86,"And when those who associated others with Allāh see their "
  16,87,"And they will impart to Allāh that Day [their] submission, and lost from them is what they used to invent."
  17,52,"On the Day He will call you and you will respond with praise of Him and think that you had not remained [in the world] except for a little."
  17,53,"And tell My servants to say that which is best. Indeed, Satan induces [dissension] among them. Indeed Satan is ever, to mankind, a clear enemy."
  17,54,"Your Lord is most knowing of you. If He wills, He will have mercy upon you; or if He wills, He will punish you. And We have not sent you, [O Muḥammad], over them as a manager."
  18,19,"And similarly,{1} We awakened them that they might question one another. Said a speaker from among them, ",footnotes:1:By the will of Allāh.
  18,20,"Indeed, if they come to know of you, they will stone you or return you to their religion. And never would you succeed, then - ever."
  18,21,"And similarly, We caused them to be found that they [who found them] would know that the promise of Allāh is truth and that of the Hour there is no doubt. [That was] when they{1} disputed among themselves about their affair and [then] said, ",footnotes:1:The people of the city.,footnotes:2:i.e., we will make this site a place of worship.